<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[73574]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Works that escape from the museum]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Activity.</strong> Discover some of the pieces in the MACBA collection on display in public spaces and create one of your own.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The MACBA has organised a summer activity with the challenge of learning to interpret pieces in its collection that have been conceived to be viewed in public spaces or spaces for getting round the museum. For example, the one inspired by a mural that Keith Haring did in Barcelona 25 years ago, which can now be seen outside the museum.</p>
<p>The workshop presents us with the challenge of collectively creating a similar artistic work. It also encourages us to think about the materials used and the relationship of the public to these works of art, located in the most unusual places. During the summer months, families can take part in it on Wednesdays.</p>
